RUGBY UNION - ENGLISH RFU APPROVES FIVE NATIONS DEAL . The English Rugby Football Union ( RFU ) on Friday formally approved a television deal which preserved England ' s Five Nations status . Cliff Brittle , chairman of the RFU executive committee , brokered the last - ditch deal with Wales , Scotland and Ireland which staved off England ' s expulsion from the championship . On Friday he persuaded the RFU committee members to ratify the agreement , which is still subject to debate by the Five Nations committee in Dublin on Monday . 
